requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall connect to the hospital LAN via an Ethernet connection when attached to the dock.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify timing, conditions for automatic connection, retry logic, or expected connection time.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify that upon docking, the system SHALL automatically establish an Ethernet link within X seconds and retry up to Y times on failure.

issues.description: No acceptance criteria defined to verify that the system is connected when docked (e.g., link status indicator).
issues.suggested_fix: Define an acceptance test such as 'verify that network link status is up within X seconds of docking'.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall have LCD that displays numerical values derived from the data acquired at the analog outputs received from the pods.

issues.description: Refers to 'analog outputs' from pods, but REQ-003 specifies digital data transfer through 14-pin connectors. This creates a conflict about the data transmission method.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether pods send analog or digital signals. Change to 'digital data' if using 14-pin connectors, or specify analog-to-digital conversion if pods output analog signals.

issues.description: It is unclear which numerical values (which specific vitals) and how analog signals are converted and validated before display.
issues.suggested_fix: List the specific vital measurements (e.g., heart rate, blood pressure) and describe the A/D conversion requirements.

issues.description: No defined criteria on accuracy or format of displayed values for verification.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify acceptable error margin and number of decimal places for numeric display.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall allow pods to transfer vital data back to the PMS through 14-Pin connectors.

issues.description: Acronym 'PMS' is not defined in the requirements. While it likely stands for 'Patient Monitoring System', this should be explicit.
issues.suggested_fix: Replace 'PMS' with 'Patient Monitoring System' or define the acronym clearly in the requirements document.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall have a port for the pod that records pulse.

issues.description: Does each pod type require a dedicated port? How is the port distinguished or configured for pulse measurement?
issues.suggested_fix: Define port properties, including a PodType enumeration specifying 'PULSE'.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall display heart rate.

issues.description: It is not specified whether heart rate is displayed numerically, graphically, or both.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify that heart rate is displayed numerically on the LCD and optionally as a waveform.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall display respiratory wave form.

issues.description: The domain model lacks a method to render waveform data on the LCD.
issues.suggested_fix: Add a method `LCD.displayWaveform(label: String, dataPoints: List<Float>)` and link `processHealthData` to it.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall allow hospital personnel to define the range of heart rate.

issues.description: The range configuration uses a generic string 'vitalType' instead of a typed VitalType enumeration.
issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a `VitalType` enum with values like `HEART_RATE` and use it in `defineVitalRange` parameters.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall trigger alarms when the patient's vitals are outside the range that hospital personnel defined.

issues.description: `triggerAlarm()` has no context of which vital triggered the alarm; lacks parameters or linkage to VitalType.
issues.suggested_fix: Modify to `triggerAlarm(vitalType: VitalType, currentValue: Float)` or add an `Alarm.associatedVital` attribute.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall not trigger alarms when the patient's vitals are within the ranges that hospital personnel defined.

issues.description: This requirement is redundant given REQ-020. If alarms trigger when vitals are outside the defined range, they logically won't trigger when vitals are within range.
issues.suggested_fix: Remove this requirement or rephrase to add value, such as specifying alarm reset behavior or confirming normal operation indicators.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The LCD screen shall show the EGG strip in a green color (using hexadecimal color code: #00FF00).

issues.description: Typo 'EGG strip' should be 'ECG strip', and the model lacks a separate ECG waveform color attribute.
issues.suggested_fix: Correct 'EGG' to 'ECG', and add an `LCD.ecgWaveFormColor` property if waveform color differs from numeric display.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The LCD shall show the vitals record in a table format.

issues.description: The requirement lacks specificity about the format of the table (columns, headers, sorting, pagination, number of rows).
issues.suggested_fix: Specify table structure details such as column headers (time, heart rate, blood pressure, etc.), number of rows to display, sorting behavior, and pagination or maximum rows per view.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall make an audible noise that is between 50 and 60 decibels when an alarm is triggered.

issues.description: No specification for duration, tone frequency, or repetition pattern of the alarm sound.
issues.suggested_fix: Define alarm duration, tone frequency, and silence intervals if the alarm repeats.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall not make an audible noise when an alarm is not triggered.

issues.description: This requirement is redundant given REQ-030. If the system makes noise when alarms are triggered, it logically won't make alarm noise when they're not triggered.
issues.suggested_fix: Remove this requirement or rephrase to specify that the system should have normal operational sounds (button clicks, startup sounds, etc.) that are distinct from alarm sounds.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall store locally the last 24 hours of data received from pods (sensors).

issues.description: The storage medium, capacity, and data retention policy are not specified.
issues.suggested_fix: Define a `LocalDataStore` with capacity for 24 hours, persistence details, and cleanup policy.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall allow the users to choose the language to display in, with the default being English.

issues.description: No method exists to set or change `defaultLanguage` at runtime.
issues.suggested_fix: Add `PatientMonitoringSystem.setLanguage(language: Language)` and validate against `languageOptions`.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall have a two-hour battery life.

issues.description: Battery life units and discharge conditions (e.g., continuous operation profile) are not specified.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify that `batteryLife` equals 120 minutes under normal operating conditions and outline the test profile.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The patient-monitoring system records shall be stored in Patient Records Systems (EMR).

issues.description: Frequency and trigger for storing records are not defined (real-time, batch, on-demand?).
issues.suggested_fix: Specify whether storage occurs in real time, at regular intervals, or upon specific events.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system in one-minute intervals, shall send record updates to the Patient Records System database of the field data for heart rate.

issues.description: The mechanism to schedule one-minute interval updates is not represented in the model.
issues.suggested_fix: Enhance `sendRecordUpdates(vitalType: VitalType, interval: Duration)` and implement a scheduler component.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall be compatible with Epic EMR.

issues.description: Compatibility criteria (interface protocol, data format) with Epic EMR are not defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify that the system SHALL conform to HL7 FHIR API versions X and Y used by Epic EMR.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall have a unique identifier code to identify each patient.

issues.description: Both `PatientMonitoringSystem` and `Patient` classes define `uniqueIdentifierCode`, causing duplication.
issues.suggested_fix: Remove or rename `PatientMonitoringSystem.uniqueIdentifierCode` (e.g., `systemID`); keep `Patient.uniqueIdentifierCode` for patients.

issues.description: The requirement doesn't specify the format, length, or generation method for the unique identifier code.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the identifier format (e.g., alphanumeric, length requirements, whether it's hospital-generated or system-generated, and if it follows any healthcare standards like MRN format).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The patient-monitoring system shall share the vitals to the Central Patient-monitoring System through the hospital's LAN.

issues.description: `shareVitals()` has no destination parameter or scheduling logic.
issues.suggested_fix: Update to `shareVitals(target: CentralPatientMonitoringSystem, interval: Duration)` to include transport settings.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall be compliant with NFPA standards.

issues.description: Specific NFPA standard numbers or sections are not specified.
issues.suggested_fix: Enumerate NFPA standard numbers (e.g., NFPA 99) and map compliance requirements to system components.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall not receive software updates when connected to a patient.

issues.description: The condition 'connected to a patient' is ambiguous and no system state exists to inhibit software updates during monitoring.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the condition (e.g., 'when actively monitoring a patient') and introduce a `SystemState` (e.g., `CONNECTED_TO_PATIENT`) to guard `receiveSoftwareUpdates()` accordingly, allowing critical security updates as needed.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The patient-monitoring system's ethernet connection shall be capable of 100 Mbps while connected to the dock.

issues.description: Ethernet speed appears in both `PatientMonitoringSystem.ethernetConnectionSpeed` and `EthernetConnection.speed`, leading to duplication.
issues.suggested_fix: Remove `ethernetConnectionSpeed` from `PatientMonitoringSystem` and rely on `EthernetConnection.speed`, enforcing a minimum of 100 Mbps.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall come with documentation containing battery pack guide to demonstrate how to install and charge the battery.

issues.description: `Documentation.docType` is generic; no enumerated guide types are defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a `DocType` enum (e.g., `BATTERY_PACK_GUIDE`) and require `Documentation` instances for each guide type.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall undergo multiple forms of testing including electrical testing and end to end testing.

issues.description: The requirement is vague about what constitutes 'multiple forms of testing' and doesn't specify testing standards or criteria for pass/fail.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the complete list of required tests, applicable standards (e.g., IEC 60601 for medical electrical equipment), and acceptance criteria for each test type.

issues.description: Testing types are passed as free-form strings to `performTesting()`, with no structured enumeration.
issues.suggested_fix: Define a `TestType` enum with values `ELECTRICAL` and `END_TO_END` and change `performTesting(testType: TestType)`.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data encryption and secure communications
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall encrypt all patient data at rest and in transit using industry-standard algorithms (e.g., AES-256 for data at rest and TLS 1.2 or higher for data in transit), authenticate to external systems using hospital-issued digital certificates, maintain encrypted communications with the hospital LAN and EMR, and implement network intrusion detection as required by hospital IT personnel.
missing_requirements.rationale: HIPAA Security Rule mandates encryption of protected health information both at rest and in transit, and hospital IT policies require secure protocols and intrusion detection to protect patient data.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for user authentication and role-based access control
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall require users to authenticate with unique secure credentials and enforce role-based access control, restricting privileges for actions such as accessing or modifying patient data, defining vital ranges, acknowledging or silencing alarms, and viewing audit logs according to user roles defined by hospital IT personnel.
missing_requirements.rationale: To comply with HIPAA and prevent unauthorized access or modification, the system must ensure that only authorized personnel with appropriate roles can perform sensitive operations.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for pod identification, status monitoring, and failure detection
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall uniquely identify each attached pod by its ID, continuously monitor its operational status, detect when a pod becomes disconnected or fails to transmit data for more than 30 seconds, display a clear notification on the LCD indicating the affected port and nature of the failure, and trigger an alarm to alert hospital personnel.
missing_requirements.rationale: Reliable patient monitoring requires that all sensor pods are correctly identified and their status tracked; detecting disconnections or failures prevents the system from using stale or missing data and supports timely intervention.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system initialization, docking events, and power/network transitions
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: Upon power-up or dock-attach/detach events, the system shall perform automated self-diagnostics, verify all connected pods, establish or tear down network connectivity, switch automatically between battery and external DC power as appropriate, require user authentication before entering operational mode, and display current power source and network status on the LCD.
missing_requirements.rationale: Defining startup sequences and handling dock events ensures seamless power and network transitions, supports uninterrupted monitoring, and enforces security before operation.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for periodic self-diagnostics and built-in self-testing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall perform built-in self-tests (electrical checks, sensor loop verification, software checksum) at power-up and at scheduled intervals (e.g., every 24 hours), report any detected faults to hospital IT systems, and prevent monitoring until critical failures are resolved.
missing_requirements.rationale: Regular self-diagnostics are essential for proactive maintenance of a medical device, ensuring ongoing reliability and early detection of failures.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data validation and physiologic plausibility checks
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall validate all incoming vital sign data from pods for physiologically plausible ranges and data integrity, reject or quarantine invalid readings, queue or retry transmissions as appropriate, and alert hospital personnel to potential sensor malfunctions.
missing_requirements.rationale: Ensuring the quality and plausibility of patient data is critical for patient safety and clinical decision-making, preventing erroneous or out-of-range readings from causing misdiagnosis.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for sampling rates of sensor data acquisition
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall sample analog data from pulse and oximeter pods at a minimum rate of 1 Hz, from blood pressure pods at a minimum rate of 1 Hz, and from ECG telemetry leads at a minimum rate of 500 Hz to ensure clinically accurate real-time monitoring.
missing_requirements.rationale: Adhering to established minimum sampling frequencies is necessary for accurate and timely detection of physiologic events in clinical monitoring.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system response time and display refresh rate
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall process and display updated vital sign measurements within 1 second of data acquisition from pods and refresh the LCD display at least every 2 seconds.
missing_requirements.rationale: Fast processing and timely updates are essential for clinical staff to make informed decisions based on the most current patient data.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data transmission frequency to central monitoring system
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall transmit updated vital sign data to the Central Patient Monitoring System every 10 seconds in JSON over TCP/IP format, including timestamp and patient identifier.
missing_requirements.rationale: Defining transmission frequency and format ensures consistent, timely data flow for central aggregation and monitoring.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data synchronization and offline operation
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: When network connectivity is unavailable, the system shall store vital sign data locally, queue outgoing records, automatically retry transmission every 30 seconds, and synchronize all cached data with the EMR and Central Patient Monitoring System when connectivity is restored.
missing_requirements.rationale: Automatic data caching, retry logic, and synchronization are required to prevent loss of patient data during network outages.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for Communication and Power Module integration
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall interface with the external Communication and Power Module to provide extended network connectivity options and manage backup power during patient transport scenarios.
missing_requirements.rationale: Integration with external modules is critical for ensuring continuous connectivity and power availability during patient transport.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system availability and reliability
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall maintain 99.9% uptime during patient monitoring periods and automatically recover from software failures within 30 seconds without data loss.
missing_requirements.rationale: High availability and rapid recovery are essential for continuous patient care and preventing monitoring interruptions.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for configuration backup and restore
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall automatically back up all configuration settings (e.g., vital sign ranges, language preferences, user settings) to the hospital LAN and restore them after system updates or hardware replacements.
missing_requirements.rationale: Preserving configuration across updates and replacements ensures consistent operation and reduces manual reconfiguration efforts.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for audit logging and compliance reporting
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall maintain audit logs of all user access events (e.g., logins, configuration changes, alarm acknowledgments), store logs locally and transmit them to the EMR or hospital IT for compliance reporting, retaining logs for at least six years.
missing_requirements.rationale: HIPAA audit control requirements mandate tracking of user actions and configuration changes for accountability and compliance.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system event logging and troubleshooting support
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall log critical system events—including sensor errors, network disconnections, power-source changes, and alarm activations—to an on-device log file with timestamps and error codes for troubleshooting and preventive maintenance.
missing_requirements.rationale: Comprehensive event logging is necessary for IT and maintenance personnel to diagnose issues, perform trend analysis, and ensure system reliability.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for emergency power-off and graceful shutdown procedures
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall include an emergency power-off function that is readily accessible but protected against accidental activation, and when battery power falls below a critical threshold, perform a graceful shutdown preserving all cached data and system state, then automatically resume monitoring when power is restored.
missing_requirements.rationale: Emergency shutdown and data preservation procedures are vital for patient safety and integrity of recorded data.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for external DC power specifications
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The external DC power source shall provide 12 V DC at a minimum of 2 A, with voltage regulation within ±5% and built-in overcurrent protection.
missing_requirements.rationale: Specifying electrical characteristics ensures safe and reliable operation when the device is powered from external sources.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for battery recharge time
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall recharge its integrated lithium battery to at least 90% capacity within 3 hours when connected to external DC power via the docking station.
missing_requirements.rationale: Defining a maximum recharge time ensures the device is ready for use in a predictable timeframe during clinical operations.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for comprehensive alarm management (acknowledgment, escalation, differentiation, visual cues)
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall allow authorized hospital personnel to acknowledge and silence active alarms through the user interface, log the acknowledgment time and user ID, escalate alarms through distinct audible and visual patterns based on severity, display a flashing red border or icon for active alarms on the LCD, and prevent silencing of critical alarms for longer than 2 minutes.
missing_requirements.rationale: Proper alarm acknowledgment, escalation, and differentiation are essential to ensure caregivers respond promptly and correctly to patient safety alerts.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for disinfection and material compliance
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: System surfaces and components shall be designed to withstand cleaning and disinfection with EPA-registered hospital-grade disinfectants in compliance with CDC guidelines for disinfection of healthcare equipment.
missing_requirements.rationale: Infection control requirements mandate that medical equipment be cleanable with hospital-grade disinfectants without damage to surfaces or electronic components.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for thermal monitoring and overheat protection
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall monitor its internal operating temperature and trigger an overheat alarm and safe shutdown of non-critical functions if the temperature exceeds 50 °C, in compliance with NFPA fire-safety standards.
missing_requirements.rationale: Thermal protection is required to prevent fire hazards and ensure device safety under continuous or high-load operation.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for patient identification confirmation and demographic display
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: Before beginning monitoring and data recording, the system shall require confirmation of patient identity via unique identifier code or barcode scan, allow entry of demographic information (name, date of birth), and display these details on the LCD throughout the monitoring session.
missing_requirements.rationale: Accurate patient identification is crucial to ensure that vital sign data is correctly associated with the intended patient, preventing medical errors.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for system time synchronization
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall automatically synchronize its internal clock with hospital time servers whenever connected to the hospital LAN.
missing_requirements.rationale: Accurate and consistent timestamps are critical for proper sequencing of patient data and legal record keeping.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for multi-patient support on battery power
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: When undocked and operating on battery power, the system shall maintain monitoring and data collection for all connected patients until the battery reaches critical levels.
missing_requirements.rationale: The ability to support multiple patients during transport or offline operation ensures continuity of care across multiple monitoring points.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for battery level monitoring and low-level warnings
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall continuously monitor batteryLife, display remaining battery percentage and estimated time remaining on the LCD, and provide visual and audible warnings when battery level drops below 15% capacity or when estimated time remaining is less than 10 minutes.
missing_requirements.rationale: Providing clear battery status information and low-level warnings is essential for planning uninterrupted monitoring and preventing unexpected shutdowns.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for display brightness adjustment
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall allow authorized users to adjust LCD brightness between 0 and 300 cd/m² to accommodate different ambient lighting conditions in patient care areas.
missing_requirements.rationale: Adjustable display brightness improves usability and readability in varying lighting environments within healthcare facilities.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data retention and purging policy
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall automatically purge locally cached patient data after 72 hours unless specifically archived by authorized personnel.
missing_requirements.rationale: HIPAA requires clear data retention and purging policies to protect patient privacy and manage storage safely.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for data format standard for EMR integration
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: All patient vitals and record updates sent to the Patient Records System shall be formatted according to HL7 v2.x or FHIR standards to ensure interoperability with EMR systems such as Epic.
missing_requirements.rationale: Standardized message formats are necessary for reliable integration with electronic medical record systems.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for software update authenticity verification
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall verify the digital signature and integrity of each software update package using cryptographic keys managed by hospital IT before installation.
missing_requirements.rationale: Verifying software update authenticity prevents installation of malicious code and supports cybersecurity best practices under HIPAA Security Rule.

domain_model_issues.description: The uniqueIdentifierCode attribute is duplicated on PatientMonitoringSystem and Patient classes, but REQ-047 specifies this should identify the patient only.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Remove uniqueIdentifierCode from PatientMonitoringSystem; if tracking system identity is required, add a new systemId attribute distinct from patientUniqueIdentifierCode.

domain_model_issues.description: The Port class lacks an attribute to indicate which Pod type it accepts, preventing differentiation of ports (pulse, pressure, oximeter, telemetry) as per REQ-004 to REQ-007.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a supportedPodType attribute (e.g., PodType enum with values PULSE, PRESSURE, OXIMETER, TELEMETRY) to the Port class.

domain_model_issues.description: No class exists to represent the vital sign threshold ranges defined by hospital personnel (min/max) as required by REQ-016 to REQ-021.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Create a VitalRange class with attributes vitalType: VitalType, minValue: Float, maxValue: Float and associate it with HospitalPersonnel and PatientMonitoringSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: Ethernet connection speed is duplicated in PatientMonitoringSystem and EthernetConnection classes, leading to redundancy and potential inconsistency (REQ-056).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Remove ethernetConnectionSpeed from PatientMonitoringSystem and use EthernetConnection.speed exclusively.

domain_model_issues.description: Both PatientMonitoringSystem and LCD classes define displayValue methods with identical signatures, causing confusion about responsibility (REQ-002, REQ-008 to REQ-011).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Remove displayValue from PatientMonitoringSystem, delegate display operations to LCD.displayValue, and update the system to call LCD.displayValue.

domain_model_issues.description: The many-to-many relationship between Pod and Connector14Pin is incorrect; each Pod should connect to exactly one Connector14Pin (REQ-003).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Change the association to a one-to-one relationship between Pod and Connector14Pin, or integrate Connector14Pin into the Port class.

domain_model_issues.description: No class models individual vital sign readings (value, type, timestamp, unit) from pods, making it impossible to represent measured data (REQ-002, REQ-008 to REQ-011, REQ-013 to REQ-015, REQ-032, REQ-041 to REQ-045).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Create a VitalSignMeasurement class with attributes vitalType: VitalType, value: Float, timestamp: DateTime, unit: String.

domain_model_issues.description: The Battery class's batteryLife attribute lacks unit documentation and default value, but REQ-037 specifies a 2-hour battery life.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Document batteryLife unit as minutes, set default value to 120, or rename batteryLife to remainingBatteryLife and add a maxBatteryLife attribute with value 120.

domain_model_issues.description: No class models local storage for caching 24 hours of vital sign data before transmission (REQ-032, REQ-033).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a LocalDataStore class with attributes capacity: Duration and records: List<VitalSignMeasurement>.

domain_model_issues.description: The model lacks representation of regulatory compliance requirements (NFPA, OSHA, HIPAA) (REQ-049 to REQ-052).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Define a RegulatoryStandard enum or class and associate relevant standards with PatientMonitoringSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: No enumeration exists for supported display languages (English, Spanish, French) as required by REQ-034 and REQ-035.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Create a Language enum and use it for defaultLanguage and languageOptions in PatientMonitoringSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: The model uses free-form strings for documentation types instead of an enumeration (REQ-058 to REQ-062).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Define a DocType enum and replace Documentation.docType: String with DocType.

domain_model_issues.description: No structured enumeration exists for test types, leading to free-form input in performTesting() (REQ-063).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Create a TestType enum (e.g., ELECTRICAL, END_TO_END) and use it for performTesting().

domain_model_issues.description: The composition relationship implies docking station ownership by the system, but a Dock is an external accessory (REQ-001, REQ-038).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Change the relationship between PatientMonitoringSystem and Dock to a simple association.

domain_model_issues.description: triggerAlarm() has no parameters or context to identify which vital sign triggered the alarm (REQ-020).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Redefine signature to triggerAlarm(vitalType: VitalType, currentValue: Float).

domain_model_issues.description: sendRecordUpdates() lacks parameters to select vital type or reporting interval, conflicting with per-vital and timed update requirements (REQ-041 to REQ-045).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Redefine signature to sendRecordUpdates(vitalType: VitalType, interval: Duration).

domain_model_issues.description: No API exists to retrieve the locally cached 24-hour vital sign data for display (REQ-033).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add retrieveLocalData(): List<VitalSignMeasurement> to PatientMonitoringSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: No method allows changing the display language at runtime (REQ-034, REQ-035).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Implement setLanguage(language: Language) on PatientMonitoringSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: Alarm class lacks an attribute linking it to a specific vital type or measurement, preventing context for alarms (REQ-020).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add associatedVital: VitalType to the Alarm class.

domain_model_issues.description: soundLevel has no validation to ensure it meets the 50–60 dB requirement (REQ-030).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add validation or setter logic to enforce soundLevel within 50–60 dB.

domain_model_issues.description: LCD class lacks a method for waveform rendering, despite requirements for waveform display (REQ-013 to REQ-015).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add displayWaveform(label: String, data: List<Float>) method to LCD.

domain_model_issues.description: The realization relationship with LinuxOperatingSystem is semantically incorrect; software hosting should be modeled as dependency or deployment (REQ-055).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Change the relationship to a dependency or deployment relationship between PatientMonitoringSystem and LinuxOperatingSystem.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The system shall connect to the hospital LAN via an Ethernet connection when attached to the dock.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Add full metadata (Priority, Version, Status, Source, Dependencies) and define measurable acceptance criteria. For example: "REQ-001 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Source: Clinical Team; Dependencies: REQ-056): The system shall connect to the hospital LAN via a 100 Mbps full-duplex Ethernet connection within 5 seconds of attachment to the dock, with auto-negotiation. Acceptance Criteria: connection established and authenticated within 5 s, IP address assigned, link status indicator displays 'Connected'. Rationale: ensures timely, reliable data transmission and traceability."
requirement_completeness.rationale: Currently missing metadata for priority, version, status, source, dependencies and lacks testable criteria (speed, timing, authentication, IP assignment), making it ambiguous and untestable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The system shall have LCD that displays numerical values derived from the data acquired at the analog outputs received from the pods.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Include metadata (Priority, Version, Status, Source, Dependencies) and specify display accuracy, timing and update frequency. For example: "REQ-002 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Source: Clinical Team; Dependencies: REQ-003, REQ-004-007): The system shall have an LCD that displays numerical values derived from analog pod outputs with ±2% accuracy, updated within 1 s of acquisition and refreshed every 500 ms. Acceptance Criteria: value accuracy within ±2%, display latency ≤1 s, refresh interval 500 ms. Rationale: ensures clear, timely, and accurate vital sign presentation."
requirement_completeness.rationale: Lacks priority, version, status, source, dependencies and measurable acceptance criteria for accuracy, latency, and refresh rate; without these details it is ambiguous and untestable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The system shall allow pods to transfer vital data back to the PMS through 14-Pin connectors.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: Add metadata and define performance and integrity requirements. For example: "REQ-003 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Source: Device Team; Dependencies: REQ-004-007): The system shall allow pods to transfer vital data via 14-Pin connectors at ≥1 kHz sampling rate with error rate <0.01% and data reception within 500 ms of transmission. Acceptance Criteria: data rate ≥1 kHz, packet error rate <0.01%, reception latency ≤500 ms, connection verification within 2 s. Rationale: ensures reliable, high-fidelity sensor data acquisition and testability."
requirement_completeness.rationale: Missing metadata for traceability and lacks specifics on data rate, error handling, latency and verification, making it ambiguous and untestable.

reasoning.domain_model: Combined core classes from all models under unified naming (PatientMonitoringSystem instead of generic System), included Device (Pod, Port, Connector14Pin), Infrastructure (Dock, EthernetConnection, HospitalLAN, ExternalDCPower, Battery, LinuxOperatingSystem), and Support (LCD, Documentation, Alarm), plus domain entities (Patient, HospitalPersonnel, PatientRecordsSystem, CentralPatientMonitoringSystem). Merged attributes and methods to capture full functionality (data recording, display, power management, communications, configuration, alarms, storage, updates, testing). Resolved duplicates by consolidating uniqueIdentifierCode on Patient and System, unified power flows via Battery and ExternalDCPower, preserved roles of Documentation and OS. Relationships reflect composition vs association per ownership and multiplicities from original models, yielding a consistent, comprehensive domain view.
reasoning.analysis:
Analysis aggregated using openai with specialized component processing:
- requirement_completeness: Reviewed three source assessments (Claude, OpenAI, DeepSeek) which provided identical completeness scores, missing elements, suggestions, and rationales for each requirement. Adopted a conservative stance by retaining the (identical) scores, merged all missing elements into unique lists, and preserved suggested improvements and rationales verbatim to ensure comprehensive coverage and traceability.
- requirement_issues: Combined and consolidated requirement issues from two analysis sources. Mapped original issue types Ambiguity, Missing Context, Testability, and Implementation to 'Missing' to comply with allowed types. Kept 'Inconsistency' issues for conflicts. Preserved all unique issues; where both sources reported the same issue (e.g., REQ-028 typo, REQ-029 format), merged details and used the most comprehensive description and suggested fix. For requirements with both context and model consistency issues (e.g., REQ-047, REQ-063), retained separate entries. For REQ-054, merged ambiguity and missing model state into a single comprehensive issue. Ensured each requirement entry includes all issues with consolidated affected model elements and consistent severity levels.
- missing_requirements: We reviewed the three provided source analyses (from Claude, OpenAI, and Deepseek), found that each source listed 29 identical missing requirements. We merged duplicates by preserving all unique requirement IDs (MR1 through MR29) and retained the most detailed descriptions, suggested requirements, affected model elements, and rationales from the sources.
- domain_model_issues: Consolidated overlapping entries from both analyses by aligning element names and mapping issue types to the standardized set (Missing, Incomplete, Inconsistent), used stricter severity levels in conflicts, merged affected requirements, and preserved unique issues. Each issue includes the most detailed description and suggested fix from both sources to ensure comprehensive coverage.
